.TH "qib_wait_linkstate" 9 "qib_wait_linkstate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
qib_wait_linkstate \- wait for an IB link state change to occur
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" qib_wait_linkstate
.BI "(struct qib_pportdata *ppd "  ","
.BI "u32 state "  ","
.BI "int msecs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ppd" 12
the qlogic_ib device
.IP "state" 12
the state to wait for
.IP "msecs" 12
the number of milliseconds to wait
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
wait up to msecs milliseconds for IB link state change to occur for
now, take the easy polling route.  Currently used only by
qib_set_linkstate.  Returns 0 if state reached, otherwise
-ETIMEDOUT state can have multiple states set, for any of several
transitions.
